snippet.textDisplay:
As a backpacker, I'm just wondering how heavy your packs are gonna be. Like that stove did not look small enough to fit in your pack. Also 35 isn't that big. I'd probably go with a 50 liter pack. More room. Still they make smaller camping stoves that are gas powered. That's more practical than wood burning.
Also I'd get an extra bladder for water. You gotta think about water sources. Is there one close enough or is the next one hours out?
Definitely carry more food. Beef jerky, cheese, nuts, tortillas and peanut butter.
Also be sure the sleeping bag actually is cold weather appropriate. Is it good for 10 degrees? Trust me it makes a difference.
And definitely take a pair of sandals for when your feet need a break from your boots.
